radiographic_examinations.findings: Minimal dependent atelectasis in the left lower lobe. No pleural or pericardial effusion. Hypodense lesion measures 0.9 x 0.7 cm in segment 7. Appendix in retrocecal position, fluid-filled and dilated measuring a maximum diameter of 1.2 cm with adjacent fatty stranding. No adjacent fluid collection or extraluminal air. Hypodense focus at the posterior uterine fundus likely reflects a fibroid, measuring 1 cm in diameter. No evidence of focal renal lesions, hydronephrosis, or lymphadenopathy.
